        <updateDate>2024-03-18T20:21:20Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Made in the U.S.A. Act &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill allows certain individual taxpayers whose adjusted gross income does not exceed $125,000 ($250,000 in the case of a joint return) a tax credit for 30% of their expenditures, not exceeding $2,500, for products made in the United States. An expenditure for any product may not exceed $500 and excludes firearms, ammunition, alcohol, tobacco, vehicles, gasoline, luxury goods, food, or non-depreciable real property. The expenditure limit is increased to $1,000 for Energy Star or climate resilience products.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
